<font color="#FF0000">OLIVE ME WHY NOT TAKE OLIVE ME</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug 21 23:29:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Sparrowhawk,<br>
     I haven't worn any olive drab skivvies and undershirts in 26 years.  At this point, I can't remember whether I bought them or was issued them. And as I said, Gloria couldn't get rid of them fast enough.<br>
     Looks like you're ahead of me on several points.  Have 2 sons and a daughter, a beautiful wife of 26 years who wants a separation to find herself, no car, a 3 story handyman's special and 2 1/2 years before retirement and a start on a masters in geography.  All things considered though, I haven't faired badly.  ...And I get to help spend part of the $3.8 billion per year that NAVICP puts into Naval Aviation spare parts (and that includes stuff for all those Marine Air Groups - visited MAG 39 at Camp Pendleton 4 years ago).  
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


